message.content:
Rule Learning. 

Explanation: The paper is focused on learning non-recursive, function-free first-order Horn definitions, which are a type of logical rule. The paper discusses how this class of rules can be learned using equivalence and membership queries, which are common techniques in rule learning. The results of the paper are also shown to be applicable to learning efficient goal-decomposition rules in planning domains, further emphasizing the focus on rule learning.
